# CodeForge project map

## Monorepo layout

- `apps/web` — Next.js 14 app (marketing + product UI)
- `services/api` — FastAPI backend
- `packages/ui` — `@codeforge/ui` React primitives (use instead of ad-hoc buttons/panels)
- `packages/design-tokens` — CSS tokens (`tokens.css`)
- `packages/shared` — shared API client helpers

## Canonical dev commands

```bash
npm run stack:up          # full Docker microservices (db, api, worker, web, gateway)
npm run stack:up:backend  # API stack only; pair with npm run dev:web:fresh on host
npm run dev:web:fresh     # clear .next + Next on :3000 (frees port first)
npm run audit:web:ci      # wait for web/API then route audit
```

See `docs/microservices.md` for gateway (:8080) vs direct ports.

## UI conventions

- Product chrome (`AppShell`, nav, topbar): **Lucide icons via `@codeforge/ui` Icon/NavItem** — no emoji in navigation.
- Shells: `marketing-shell` (landing), `app-shell` (product, including `/code`), `minimal-shell` (login, share, onboarding).
- Session deep links: `?s=<session_id>` shared between `/app` and `/code`.
- Design tokens: import `@codeforge/design-tokens/tokens.css`; avoid hardcoded colors in new CSS.

## API / web integration

- Default API: `http://localhost:8000` via `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE`.
- CORS allows `localhost:3000` and `127.0.0.1:3000`.
- Readiness: `GET /ready` (postgres + redis); liveness: `GET /health`.
- Optional BFF: set `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_DIRECT=false` to proxy via `/api/proxy/*`.

## Backend conventions

- Python 3.13, FastAPI, pytest in `services/api`.
- Platform routes in `services/api/app/routers/platform.py`.
- DB access via `app/db.py` (`ping_db()` for readiness).

## Testing

- API: `npm run api:test` (pytest in `services/api`)
- Web: `npm run lint:web`, `npm run build:web` (no Jest unit tests in web workspace)
- Web route audit: `npm run audit:web`
- VS Code ext: `npm run check:vscode`
- Desktop: `cargo check` in `apps/desktop/src-tauri`
- E2E: `npm run test:e2e` (Playwright)
- A11y: `npm run test:a11y`
- CI order: api-tests → web-audit (build + route audit) → e2e-smoke

## Loop Engineering

Autonomous verify/fix after code changes: see `.cursor/rules/loop-engineering.mdc` and `.codeforge/loop-engineering.yaml` (max **5** attempts).

## Magic Pointer

Cursor-aware context and deictic language ("this", "that"): `.cursor/rules/magic-pointer.mdc`, `.codeforge/magic-pointer.yaml`, **Ctrl+Shift+G** on `/code`.
